via a theory termed,

22
00:01:20,593 --> 00:01:22,010
"The Diffusion of Innovations."

23
00:01:22,210 --> 00:01:26,053
Diffusion of Innovations is a theory
that seeks to explain how,

24
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:29,703
why and at what rate new ideas
and technology spread?

25
00:01:29,903 --> 00:01:33,887
This theory was popularized
by Prof. Everett Rogers in his book

26
00:01:34,087 --> 00:01:36,316
that was first published in 1962,

27
00:01:36,516 --> 00:01:38,824
and is now in its fifth edition
and beyond.

28
00:01:39,024 --> 00:01:42,691
The process of adoption over time
is typically illustrated

29
00:01:42,804 --> 00:01:44,445
