normal distribution

30
00:01:44,546 --> 00:01:46,160
or "bell curve".

31
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,599
The model indicates that

32
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:52,541
the first group of people to use
a new product are called Innovators,

33
00:01:52,741 --> 00:01:53,940
which you see on the left.

34
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:56,025
Followed by Early Adopters.

35
00:01:56,225 --> 00:01:58,964
Next come the Early Majority,

36
00:01:59,164 --> 00:02:00,839
and Late Majority,

37
00:02:01,039 --> 00:02:04,202
and the last group to eventually
adopt a product are called Laggards.

38
00:02:04,402 --> 00:02:07,521
Unfortunately, in reality,
the majority of innovations

39
00:02:07,624 --> 00:02:10,533
never make it past
the early adopters stage!

40
00:02:10,733 --> 00:02:14,647
So what can you possibly do
to enhance the chances of success

41
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,867
